node.text:
Just a quick reminder: changing room you is NOT the real you. 

One would assume that by making changing room lights and mirrors super flattering, big retailers would sell more because we would feel like our best selves in the new garments. But most just throw harsh fluorescent overhead lights in a claustrophobic and way too hot tiny box that has dust bunnies lying around, and the curtain doesn’t close properly, so everyone can see you half naked. 

So let’s just keep it in mind that the image the mirror shows is distorted, unrealistic, and isn’t how we EVER look outside of these torture chambers.

💪🏻
Via @lainey.molnar

node.text:
Week 2 of being at maintenance, after gaining weight for 34 weeks💪🏼
One of the main motivators of continuing my weight gain was regaining my period after 8 years of Hypothalamic Amenorrhoea, and I am SO happy to say I got my 2nd period back last Wednesday!

I got my first one back in April, so I was worried it wasn’t going to come back again BUT we persisted and gave my body the time it needed. This is why it’s SO important to not back track and start reducing your cals again after your first period comes back, and ultimately not give up. We don’t give up here!!

So this week I’m feeling a bit lighter and holding a little less water retention than last week. My strength is still increasing even though my cals aren’t, so that’s pretty cool. I have never been this strong in my life and I am LOVING feeling strong 💪🏼

⚠️ trigger warning, calories mentioned below ⚠️

🍽 My cals are still stuck at 2900
🏋🏼‍♀️ I’m starting a new workout programme next week which is 4 full body workouts focusing on the glutes, which means 3 rest days 🤩
🚲 I now do x2 LISS sessions that are 20 mins long. Very causal. Usually on a bike at a steady state
🚶🏼‍♀️I’m still reaching 9k steps and not stressing if I don’t 🌈

Really happy living life and feeling strong. This is the outcome if you JUST KEEP GOING and stick at it. It’s all SO worth it👏🏻 if I can do it, YOU CAN DO IT
-
Never miss any update from us. Don't forget to share and follow my page for more inspiration and weight loss related posts 🍀⠀⠀⠀⁣
-⠀⠀⠀⠀⁣
🔅 Save this post and share it with a friend who needs this ❤⠀
-
🍋@gains 
Cc @millyg_fit 💪💖

node.text:
Lunch Box inspo 💫🍱💫 Simple & DELICIOUS ideas! 1-5, which is your favourite?⁣
⠀⁣
Having lunch prepped ahead of time is absolutely the best feeling🥗 If you’re planning to make your lunch next week, here’s some inspo for prep this weekend☺️❤️…All by @mad_about_food⁣
⠀⁣
1.Find someone that looks at you the way I look at salmon in my lunch box😍 Chopped romaine🥬 topped with cucumbers, tomatoes and seared salmon with berries🍒& chocolate covered almonds on the side.⁣
⠀⁣
2.Seasoned chicken🍗, brown rice, sautéed kale with mixed berries and sea salt and almond dark chocolate🍫⁣
⠀⁣
3.Macadamia nuts and 85% dark chocolate, two🥚🥚hard boiled eggs, arugula salad with prosciutto, cucumber ribbons, tomatoes and mozzarella🧀⁣
⠀⁣
4.Salad with honey🍯mustard glazed chicken, sliced cucumbers and sliced avocado, clementines🍊 and a peppermint cookie bark😋⁣
⠀⁣
5.unwich with romaine, turkey, salami, feta and tomato, eggs, cucumber, goat cheese & protein bar.⁣
⠀⁣
Love to know which is your favourite 1 below!😍⁣
Is it time for lunch yet?⁣
⁣

node.text:
￼DON’T LIKE IT? DON’T CARE😜

Can we normalise being normal. Please🥺

6 months ago I would have been far too self conscious posting a relaxed photo of my tummy.

But thanks to all of your kind love & support I feel so comfortable and empowered posting content like this!

THANK YOU FAMILY🤍✨

And as for all the horrible comments I still get. Good luck trying to break this barrier 💪🏽 

Remember we have full control over how Instagram looks. Posting fun candid pics from time to time can not only help other people but it will make you feel like this… 😌

BE THE PERSON YOU WANT TO SEE ON SOCIAL MEDIA🤍✨
@karinairby
